<paragraph blockId="5.[111,649,216,1193]" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">
The sheet A 00251592 has two labels in the lower left margin: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[252,337,469,495]" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">Label 1</emphasis>
: “HERBARIUM GRAELSIANUM // PLANTAE CASTELLANAE [printed] // 
<taxonomicName authority="Wk." authorityName="Willk. &amp; Cut. (Willkomm" authorityYear="1859" box="[187,502,533,559]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Santolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="138" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="heterophylla">Santolina heterophylla Wk.</taxonomicName>
// in saxosis Sierra de Gredos et Puerto del Pico prope riventos // Julio [Graells’ handwritten notation]”; and 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[565,644,596,622]" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">Label 2</emphasis>
(printed): “HERBARIUM OF GEORGE CURLING JOAD. PRESENTED BY THE ROYAL GARDENS, KEW, 1882”. The labels do not show the collector and year. The notation of the labels does not match with the 
<typeStatus box="[391,492,754,780]" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">lectotype</typeStatus>
, however, this specimen is the counterpart of the type material of this name. 
<bibRefCitation author="Carrasco" box="[273,518,818,844]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Carrasco" pageId="5" pageNumber="138" pagination="93 - 103" refId="ref9321" refString="CARRASCO M. A., PEREA D., ARAGON C. F. &amp; GARCIA- CAMACHO R. 2002. - La coleccion &quot; Plantes de la province de Granade &quot; de Pedro del Campo, en el herbario del Real Colegio Alfonso XII de San Lorenzo de El Escorial, Madrid (Espana). Botanica Complutensis 26: 93 - 103." type="journal article" year="2002">
Carrasco 
<emphasis box="[379,434,818,844]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">et al.</emphasis>
(2002)
</bibRefCitation>
discuss the value of the collections of the 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">Real Colegio Alfonso XII</emphasis>
historical herbarium of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">San Lorenzo del Escorial</emphasis>
(
<collectingRegion box="[165,251,913,939]" country="Spain" name="Madrid" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">Madrid</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[263,328,913,940]" name="Spain" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">Spain</collectingCountry>
). They argue that the Graells’ collection was used by Willkomm &amp; Lange as part of the material examined for the 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">Prodromus florae hispanicae</emphasis>
. However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Willk. &amp; Cut. (Willkomm" authorityYear="1859" box="[341,491,1008,1034]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Santolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="138" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="heterophylla">
<emphasis box="[341,491,1008,1034]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">S. heterophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was published several years before the publication of the species corology of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[344,443,1071,1097]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Santolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="138" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[344,443,1071,1097]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">Santolina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">Prodromus florae hispanicae</emphasis>
(1865). There is not enough evidence to justify the choice of this material as original material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Willk. &amp; Cut. (Willkomm" authorityYear="1859" box="[184,335,1166,1193]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Santolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="138" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="heterophylla">
<emphasis box="[184,335,1166,1193]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">S. heterophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
